#MEM id=subagent-driven-development source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/quinn/skills/superpowers/subagent-driven-development/spec-reviewer-prompt.md
M|subagent-driven-development|Use this template when dispatching a spec compliance reviewer subagent.
M|subagent-driven-development|**Purpose:** Verify implementer built what was requested (nothing more, nothing less)
M|subagent-driven-development|```
M|subagent-driven-development|Task tool (general-purpose):
M|subagent-driven-development|description: "rv spec compliance for Task N"
M|subagent-driven-development|prompt: |
M|subagent-driven-development|You are reviewing whether an implementation matches its specification.
M|subagent-driven-development|[FULL TEXT of task requirements]
M|subagent-driven-development|[From implementer's report]
M|subagent-driven-development|The implementer finished suspiciously quickly. Their report may be incomplete,
M|subagent-driven-development|inaccurate, or optimistic. You MUST verify everything independently.
M|subagent-driven-development|**DO NOT:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- Take their word for what they implemented
M|subagent-driven-development|- Trust their claims about completeness
M|subagent-driven-development|- Accept their interpretation of requirements
M|subagent-driven-development|**DO:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- Read the actual code they wrote
M|subagent-driven-development|- Compare actual implementation to requirements line by line
M|subagent-driven-development|- Check for missing pieces they claimed to implement
M|subagent-driven-development|- Look for extra features they didn't mention
M|subagent-driven-development|Read the implementation code and verify:
M|subagent-driven-development|**Missing requirements:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- Did they implement everything that was requested?
M|subagent-driven-development|- Are there requirements they skipped or missed?
M|subagent-driven-development|- Did they claim something works but didn't actually implement it?
M|subagent-driven-development|**Extra/unneeded work:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- Did they build things that weren't requested?
M|subagent-driven-development|- Did they over-engineer or add unnecessary features?
M|subagent-driven-development|- Did they add "nice to haves" that weren't in spec?
M|subagent-driven-development|**Misunderstandings:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- Did they interpret requirements differently than intended?
M|subagent-driven-development|- Did they solve the wrong problem?
M|subagent-driven-development|- Did they implement the right feature but wrong way?
M|subagent-driven-development|**Verify by reading code, not by trusting report.**
M|subagent-driven-development|Report:
M|subagent-driven-development|- ✅ Spec compliant (if everything matches after code inspection)
M|subagent-driven-development|- ❌ Issues found: [list specifically what's missing or extra, with file:line references]
M|subagent-driven-development|```